                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.6363/1012: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Summerlin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-10-19T11:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 19, 1921—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 7:01 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>194. Department’s telegram no. 134. Texas Company’s representative furnished me
                    following data on subjects desired: <list>
                        <label>1st.</label>
                        <item>In deed to Ravise from the Martinez family petroleum rights were
                            specifically mentioned.</item>
                        <pb facs="0569" n="473" xml:id="pg_473"/>
                        <label>2d.</label>
                        <item>The Texas Company did not purchase the land but bought the lease or
                            contract from Ravise. Ravise was to have 5% of the petroleum secured
                            from the land.</item>
                        <label>3d.</label>
                        <item>Neither Texas Company nor Ravise conduct any operations on land
                            covered by contract.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Summerlin</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
